Summary an Annicchiarico object

Source: R/summary.Annicchiarico.R
summary.Annicchiarico.Rd

Summary the Annicchiarico object in two ways. By default, the results are shown in the R console. The results can also be exported to the directory into a *.txt file.

# S3 method for Annicchiarico
summary(object, export = FALSE,
  file.name = NULL, digits = 3, ...)

Arguments

object

The Annicchiarico object
export

A logical argument. If TRUE, a *.txt file is exported to the working directory.
file.name

The name of the file if export = TRUE
digits

The significant digits to be shown.
...

Other arguments of the function

Examples


library(metan)
Ann = Annicchiarico(data_ge2,
                    env = ENV,
                    gen = GEN,
                    rep = REP,
                    resp = PH)
summary(Ann)
